.SH "NAME"
pcp_log_rotate \- rotates the Pgpool\-II\*(Aqs log file
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBpcp_log_rotate\fR\ 'u
\fBpcp_log_rotate\fR [\fIoptions\fR...]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBpcp_log_rotate\fR
rotates the Pgpool\-II\*(Aqs log file\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
.PP
\fB\-s \fR\fB\fIscope\fR\fR
.br
\fB\-\-scope=\fR\fB\fIscope\fR\fR
.RS 4
Specifies the breadth of a command\*(Aqs impact\&.
.sp
The supported command scopes are as follows (The default is "local"):
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
c, cluster : rotates the Pgpool\-II\*(Aqs log files of all Pgpool\-II nodes part of the cluster
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
l, local : rotates the Pgpool\-II\*(Aqs log file of local Pgpool\-II node only
.RE
.sp
.RE
.PP
\fBOther options \fR
.RS 4
See
\fBpcp_common_options\fR(1)\&.
.RE
